text.section:
In determining if a provision of a rental agreement or of a park rule is unconscionable the court may consider if the provision:
Promotes the convenience, safety, or welfare of residents;
Preserves from abusive use property of the park owner;
Promotes a fair distribution of services or facilities held out to residents generally;
Relates reasonably to its purpose;
Applies to all residents in a fair manner;
Are sufficiently explicit for a resident to comply; and
Is for the purpose of evading an obligation of the park owner.
